com.misc.common.moplaf.solver

Interface Solver

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, IGeneratorTool, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, com.misc.common.moplaf.job.Run, com.misc.common.moplaf.job.RunParams, SolutionProvider, SolutionProviderParams, SolverParams
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SolverCp, SolverLp
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SolverCpImpl, SolverImpl, SolverLpImpl

    public interface Solver
extends SolutionProvider, SolverParams
    A representation of the model object 'Solver'.

    A Solver is a run of a concrete solver. It provides control how the run must be performed (MaxDuration, BackgroundProcess) and gives information how the run is or has been performed (timestamps, status).

    A Solver solves a given a problem formulation provided by the interface IGeneratorTool

    A Solver produces one or several Solution for the problem, as specified by its super class SolutionProvider.

    To launch the run, call the method solve().

    Solver factories can be registered with the extension com.misc.common.moplaf.solver.solver_factory and the interface SolverFactory

    The following features are supported:

    • Status
    • Solver Log Level
    • Solver Dump
    • Run Started
    • Run Initialization Ended
    • Run Solving Ended
    • Run Finalization Ended
    • Run Duration Initialization
    • Run Duration Finalization
    • Run Duration Solving
    • Run Request Terminate
    • Run Time Out
    • Sol Unfeasible
    • Sol Feasible
    • Sol Optimal
    • Sol Value
    • Run Interrupted
    • Initializing
    • Solving
    • Finalizing
    • Finished
    • Initial Solution
    • Goals
    • Var Binders
    See Also:
    SolverPackage.getSolver()
